One important factor describing the performance of the integrated hybrid system is the overall energy conversion efficiency (ηoverall). The ηoverall is defined by the ratio of effective output energy to the overall input energy. In the case of our integrated system, the effective output energy is defined by the discharge of 3D NiCo2O4 hierarchical arrays//AC BSHs; the overall input energy is defined by the illumination of AM 1.5 G. Thus, the overall energy conversion efficiency can be described as:1η=Idis∫vdtPSt\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
